[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ayr United 1-4 Greenock Morton

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Greenock Morton closed the gap on second-placed Dundee United after an emphatic away win over Ayr United.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Championship promotion chasers raced into a 3-0 lead from a Ross Forbes' double and a Gary Oliver strike.
Jamie Adams gave Ayr hope before half-time with a left-footed shot into the bottom corner.
However, Gary Oliver scored again to restore the three-goal lead and move Morton three points of second.
